        {
            "blockname": "Disability",
            "name": "Myths and Misconceptions",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Test Yourself: How much do you know about dyslexia?",
                    "space_after": true,
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Researchers know more and more about the causes and effects of dyslexia. But a few myths persist. Test yourself about knowlede on dyslexia using the quiz below. All answers are revealed when you finish the quiz, along with clarifications."
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "quiz",
                            "questions": [
                                {
                                    "index": 0,
                                    "text": "Dyslexia is a sign of low IQ.",
                                    "answers": [
                                        {
                                            "id": 0,
                                            "text": "True"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "id": 1,
                                            "text": "False"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "correct_answer": 1,
                                    "tip": "Dyslexia affects a cross section of people regardless of race, ethnicity, gender, age, intellectual level etc.  It is not an indication of low or high intelligence."
                                },
                                {
                                    "index": 1,
                                    "text": "People can grow out of dyslexia or be cured.",
                                    "answers": [
                                        {
                                            "id": 0,
                                            "text": "True"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "id": 1,
                                            "text": "False"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "correct_answer": 1,
                                    "tip": "Dyslexia is not an illness, so it cannot be cured.  Dyslexia does not go away but the right support can help to alleviate its symptoms."
                                },
                                {
                                    "index": 2,
                                    "text": "There are more male than female dyslexics. ",
                                    "answers": [
                                        {
                                            "id": 0,
                                            "text": "True"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "id": 1,
                                            "text": "False"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "correct_answer": 1,
                                    "tip": "It was thought that 4:1 were males, but it is now believed to be 50/50% "
                                },
                                {
                                    "index": 3,
                                    "text": "A person can’t be dyslexic if they read.",
                                    "answers": [
                                        {
                                            "id": 0,
                                            "text": "True"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "id": 1,
                                            "text": "False"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "correct_answer": 1,
                                    "tip": "Not true.  Many dyslexic people enjoy reading."
                                },
                                {
                                    "index": 4,
                                    "text": "Dyslexics are usually left handed.",
                                    "answers": [
                                        {
                                            "id": 0,
                                            "text": "True"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "id": 1,
                                            "text": "False"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "correct_answer": 1,
                                    "tip": "This is not true however many dyslexics have a cross-laterality issue which can cause problems."
                                },
                                {
                                    "index": 5,
                                    "text": "If you’ve been to university, you can’t be dyslexic.",
                                    "answers": [
                                        {
                                            "id": 0,
                                            "text": "True"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "id": 1,
                                            "text": "False"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "correct_answer": 1,
                                    "tip": "The number of university students with dyslexia has grown year on year.  There is DSA support available which makes a big difference.  It is not unusual for dyslexia to be identified for the first time at university."
                                }
                            ],
                            "space_after": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
